cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

This paper deals with the design of energy-efficient mechanisms in wireless small cell networks, which is a topic related to network optimization and game theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper proposes a noncooperative game among the base stations, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also proposes a cost function to capture the tradeoff between energy expenditure and load, which is related to information theory and optimization, indicating that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper presents simulation results that involve multimedia traffic, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
